    <note>Yu(1) Yan [10137] A renowned scholar of the classics who late in life turned to alchemical treatises. He was author of the Lu Chunyang Zhenren qin yuan chun dan ci zhu jie (HY, 136) and the Xuan pin zhi wen fu (4 pp., HY, 1007 [colophon by son, Zhongwen, dated 1356]) and compiled the Yi wai bie zhuan (HY 1006). Lu Xinyuan, Song shiyi, 35.6a. Check also Kinugawa Tsuyoshi's indexes to the SongYuan xuean. CBD, 2, 2680.亦據元人傳記資料索引電子版4668</note>
